729196f-a.title: Richmond: New Dorp Lane - Cedar Grove Avenue
729196f-a.text:
New Dorp Lane, at the o.W. cmne of Cedar Grove
Avenue, show ing the Britton Cottage, built before 1695. The
cottage was restored by the W.P. A. in 1939 and made a shrine.
For additonal cata see ''The New Yohk Timas,'' April 16, 1939,
Real Estate section, p. 1. Che two views were taken the
same year.

729199f-a.title: Richmond: New Dorp Lane - Cedar Grove Avenue
729199f-a.text:
(1)
New Dorp Lane, at the S.W. corner of Cedar Grove Avenue,
showing the Britton Cottage, built before 1695. It came into the
possession of Britton in 1695, and later passed through the hands of
Walton, Cubberly and Miss H. Lord. Still later it belonged to Dr.
Nathaniel Britton, who deeded it to the Staten Island Association of
Arts and Sciences in 1915.
About 1905.
By Mulford Simonson from Staten Island Museum Collection
through P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
(2)
Another view of the cottage.
About 1905.
By Mulford Simonson from Staten Island Museum Collection
through P.  L. Sperr .
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
Note: Por additional information see ''The New York Times',
April 16, 1939, Real Estate section, p. 1.
